{
  "_comment": [
    "Read-differential corpus for the character vault read overlay (hydrateOne +",
    "applyDocumentStoreOverlay). The builder seeds six pinned document stores and a file",
    "corpus via v4's real linkDocumentContent; both v4 and the Rust port READ the same",
    "fixture and run applyDocumentStoreOverlay over the same input characters, so every",
    "minted id/timestamp is identical and the hydrated characters compare exactly — EXCEPT",
    "the physicalDescription mint branch, whose createdAt/updatedAt are minted at",
    "hydration time (new Date / clock::now) and are placeholdered for the ids in",
    "mintCharacterIds.",
    "Coverage: pass-through (no linked vault); full overlay (all single files + physical",
    "base-reuse + multi-default prompts + scenario); DROP on missing properties.json;",
    "partial (properties only -> identity kept, systemPrompts/scenarios REPLACED with []);",
    "physical MINT (no existing physicalDescription); empty identity.md -> null + prompt",
    "promote-first (no default); prompt keep-non-first-default.",
    "SAFETY: testPepperBase64 is a THROWAWAY 32-byte key, the same one every tier-2",
    "fixture uses; it decrypts nothing real."
  ],
